perf: scalability hardening & solver correctness fixes

- Redis-backed distributed rate limiting with env-configurable limits
- Nginx upstream keepalive pools for all backends (reduces TCP overhead)
- Mongo pool sizing from env vars (100 max, 20 min, configurable timeouts)
- HTTP server tuning: keepAliveTimeout, headersTimeout, maxConnections
- WebSocket: prefer ws transport, 1MB message cap, per-message deflate
- V8 heap capped at 768MB to prevent OOM kills in containers
- AI session store: memory caps, cursor-based IndexedDB loading, trimming
- URL-encoded body parser with 512KB limit

Solver correctness:
- Fix shear modulus: G = E/(2(1+v)) instead of E/2.6 across 5 files
- P-Delta: proper 12x12 geometric stiffness matrix (Kassimali formulation)
- P-Delta handler: real stiffness assembly + PDeltaSolver integration
- Modal analysis: use actual K matrix instead of placeholder identity
- New Solver::assemble_global_stiffness() with parallel member contributions

All tests pass: 466 web + 186 API, TypeScript clean, cargo check clean
